						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Iṟuvaprali Paḍālu Immaḍi</hi> made a gift of one hundred cows and one bullock to god Tripurāntakadēva and fifty cows and a bullock to goddess Tripurāparamēśvari for supplying ghee for perpetual lamps, for the merit of <hi rend="bold">Annama-Reḍḍiṅgāru.</hi></p>						

